<p>This privacy policy explains how jeremyknight.me (“we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses, and protects the personal information of our visitors (“you” or “your”). 
By accessing or using this blog, you agree to this privacy policy. If you do not agree with this privacy policy, please do not use this blog.</p>

<h4>What information do we collect?</h4>

<p>We do not collect any personal information from you when you visit this blog, unless you voluntarily provide it to us. For example, if you contact us via email or 
a contact form, we may collect your name and email address.</p>

<p>We also use Microsoft Clarity, a free analytics tool that helps us understand how visitors interact with our blog. Microsoft Clarity collects data 
such as your IP address, location, browser, browser language, operating system, device identifiers, and cookies. Microsoft Clarity does not collect any personally 
identifiable information from you. You can learn more about Microsoft Clarity and its privacy practices at 
<a href="https://clarity.microsoft.com/terms" target="_blank">Microsoft Clarity</a>.</p>

<p>We have disabled cookies by default on this blog. Cookies are small files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the website remember 
your preferences and improve your user experience. You can enable cookies on this blog by clicking on the cookie consent banner at the bottom of the page. You can 
also disable cookies in your browser settings at any time.</p>

<p>We do not allow users to comment on blog posts. Therefore, we do not collect any information from user comments.</p>

<h4>How do we use the information we collect?</h4>

<p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>To respond to your inquiries and requests</li>
  <li>To improve our blog content and design</li>
  <li>To analyze user behavior and trends</li>
  <li>To comply with legal obligations and enforce our rights</li>
</ul>

<h4>How do we protect the information we collect?</h4>

<p>We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, or destruction. However, no method of 
transmission or storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.</p>

<h4>Do we share or sell the information we collect?</h4>

<p>We do not share or sell your personal information to any third parties, except as required by law or with your consent. We may share aggregated or anonymized data 
with Microsoft Clarity for analytical purposes.</p>

<h4>What rights do you have over your information?</h4>

<p>You have the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict the processing of your personal information that we hold. You also have the right to object to the processing 
of your personal information or withdraw your consent at any time.</p>

<h4>How do we update this privacy policy?</h4>

<p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. We may notify you of any material changes by posting a 
notice on our blog or by email. Your continued use of this blog after such notice constitutes your acceptance of the updated privacy policy.</p>

<h4>How can you contact us?</h4>

<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or our data practices, please contact us using one of the many social/contact links provided below.</p>

